<h1><p>How do I deal with questions I don't know how to answer?</p></h1>


<div class="rightFloatvideo1">
<tab/><video src="../media/Unit05_e4a.flv" mode="16" id="1003" autoPlay="false"/>
</div>
<p class="linespace"></p>
<div class="brieftext">
<p>1.<tab/>Be honest and tell the examiner.</p>

<ul color="#7935AB">
	
	<li>"I'm sorry, I haven't thought about that"</li>
	<li>"I don't really know much about it"</li>
	<li>"I'm not sure why it is like that"</li>
	<li>"I don't really understand what it is about"</li>
</ul>

<p><tab/>You are having a conversation, not an interrogation. You are not expected to be an encyclopaedia!</p>
<p class="linespace"></p>
<p>2.<tab/>Or, have a go, make an intelligent guess. But let the examiner know that is what you are doing:</p>

<ul color="#7935AB">
	<li>"Perhaps it could be ..."</li>
	<li>"Some people might say it is ..."</li>
	<li>"I've never really thought about it, but it could be ..."</li>
</ul>

<p>3.<tab/>Get round a difficult question by guessing, saying "maybe", or "perhaps".</p>
<p class="linespace"></p>
<p>4.<tab/>If it's Phase 1 or Phase 2, ask the Examiner to repeat the question. If it's Phase 3 of the test, you can ask the Examiner to clarify the question.</p>
</div>

<div class="rightFloatvideo1">
<tab/><video src="../media/Unit05_e4b.flv" mode="16" id="1004" autoPlay="false"/><tab/><tab/>
<video src="../media/Unit05_e4c.flv" mode="16" id="1005" autoPlay="false"/><br/>
<tab/><video src="../media/Unit05_e4d.flv" mode="16" id="1006" autoPlay="false"/>
</div>

<div class="brieftext">
<p class="linespace"></p>
<p>5.<tab/>Do not pretend to understand if you really don't know!</p>
</div>
